  "market_context": "Price was in an uptrend with successive bullish structure breaks; momentum subsided, then price broke below the most recent major low and demand zones, signaling a shift from bullish to bearish order flow.",
  "key_observation": "After breaking and closing below the most recent major low and demand zone, price formed a new supply zone at the extreme, indicating a bearish change of character and impending trend reversal.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify that price was in an uptrend with consistent bullish structure breaks.",
    "Step 2: Observe price breaking and closing below the most recent major low and latest demand zone — the first change of character.",
    "Step 3: Note price continuing downward, breaking through another demand zone and higher low — second change of character.",
    "Step 4: Recognize that each broken demand zone creates an opposite-side supply zone at the extreme.",
    "Step 5: Anticipate price retracing upward into the newly formed supply zone for a sell entry.",
    "Step 6: Confirm bearish order flow after price reversed from the supply zone and formed successive bearish breaks of structure."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A bearish change of character occurs when price breaks key structural lows and demand zones; this flips prior support into supply, enabling high-probability short entries on retests of the extreme zone.",
